        This is my personal tierlist of some tracks in the top 40.

        S TIER

        I Love You, I'm Sorry - Gracie Abrams (38). This song is emotional and beautiful, and I'm pretty sad that Gracie's breakthrough came from That's So True (3) and not this masterpiece. She's definitely my favourite artist that's in the chart at the moment, and if Close To You charted then it would be even above this one. Gracie's music is just so peaceful.

        Good Luck, Babe! - Chappell Roan (21). I'm disappointed that she didn't manage to hit number one when Sabrina Carpenter was dominating last year, because her melodic talent is so impressive. I think the lyrics are pretty clever too. A well-deserved S Tier.

        Beautiful Things - Benson Boone (40). A really good emotional ballad that I think should stay in the chart for longer. Slow It Down was fairly good when it charted but this one has to be even better.

        A TIER

        Sailor Song - Gigi Perez (5). A catchy, well-made country-pop song that I think should have got more than one week at number one but I'm glad about what came after it.

        That's So True - Gracie Abrams (3). Gracie needed a breakthrough so badly, and this was a fairly good song to do it. I would have preferred it to be I Love You, I'm Sorry (38) but I'm more than happy with her good run at number one.

        Pink Pony Club - Chappell Roan (22). Not quite at Good Luck, Babe! (21) level but still a great start to her career.

        Birds of a Feather - Billie Eilish (20). A powerful song that I think should have reached number one.

        B TIER

        APT. - Rose and Bruno Mars (2). IT'S SO CATCHY! I don't think it's as good melodically as some others but still a great song if you need an energy boost. It needs to make it to number one soon.

        PUSH 2 START - Tyla (25). A funny one more than anything. Pretty decent.

        Taste - Sabrina Carpenter (31). The most tolerable of Sabrina's work. I don't think much of the music video though.

        C TIER
        [Every other song I haven't mentioned is in here.]

        F TIER

        Like Him - Tyler the Creator (34). Just not my style of music, I think it's really hard to listen to. This one just isn't it for me - there's nothing terrible about it.

        Dirty Cash - Pawsa (17). Another really weird one I don't like at all. I can see why some like it though.

        U TIER

        Bad Chem - Sabrina Carpenter (15). No. Just no. I won't listen to this.



        ​
